Interface ICollisionEvents


  • public interface ICollisionEvents
    This interface defines events generated by the collision of GVRRigidBody.

      • onEnter

        void onEnter(GVRSceneObject sceneObj0,
             GVRSceneObject sceneObj1,
             float[] normal,
             float distance)
        Called when a Collision starts to be processed on a scene object.
        Parameters:
        sceneObj0 - GVRSceneObject with a GVRRigidBody in collision with sceneObj1
        sceneObj1 - GVRSceneObject with a GVRRigidBody in collision with sceneObj0
        normal - a float vector with the normal between the two colliding objects
        distance - distance between the objects (usually zero)
